<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1910/519640-625x325.jpg" alt="Image source: Gallo/Getty." width="625" height="325">Image source: Gallo/Getty.According to the Tema-based rapper, his new TV show is dubbed ‘H-Tunez with Opanka’ and will be broadcasted on HelloAdipa Television. He also highlighted that new TV show will engage numerous music talents as they promote their talent to the world.During an interview with Ghana News agency, he stated, “I’ve always dream of doing something as a way of giving back to society. This platform offers me the chance to engage some good talents in the country and I believe we will achieve positive results with this show.’’He added that participants who perform brilliantly will get signed onto various record labels in the country. As a result, Opanka called underground musicians to take advantage of this opportunity to showcase their talents in the showbiz industry.Source: NexTVAfrica.com.